# ViralForge AI / ForgeOS

Read `AGENTS.md`, `README.md`, all `memory-bank/*.md`, and the relevant documents under `docs/` before implementing. Use the matching `.cursor/agents/*.md` role contract and `.cursor/commands/*.md` workflow.

## Source of truth

Security/privacy > accepted ADRs > product requirements > API/data contracts > engineering specifications > implementation convenience.

## Execution

- Start from `docs/05-execution/CURSOR_MASTER_PROMPT.md`.
- Execute one backlog item at a time from the current `docs/05-execution/SPRINT_<n>_BACKLOG.md`.
- Do not begin Sprint 1 until every Sprint 0 exit gate is evidenced.
- Use bounded subagents for independent domains; one lead agent integrates and verifies.
- Make small commits tied to backlog IDs and include tests in the same change.
- Record material unspecified decisions as ADRs before implementation.
- Update the memory bank after every completed task and before every handoff.
- Do not advance any sprint until its exit gate and the Definition of Done are evidenced.

## Engineering boundaries

- Strict TypeScript and a pnpm monorepo.
- Modular monolith with separate web, API, and worker entrypoints.
- PostgreSQL is authoritative; Redis and derived media are recoverable.
- Durable binaries belong in object storage, never local Railway disk.
- AI produces schema-validated plans; deterministic code executes them.
- Every write and asynchronous job is tenant-authorized and idempotent.
- All providers must have fake adapters so local development needs no paid keys.
- Never commit secrets, private media, scraped protected data, or copyrighted audio.
- Preserve the YouTube Option 1 music handoff.

## Required proof

Do not mark work complete without commands run, test output, migration status, responsive evidence where applicable, and remaining risks. Update traceability and handoff documents as the implementation evolves.
